1: The whale cut another 5094 ETH to protect its position, and has accumulated a loss of 40 million US dollars on ETH;
2: Justin Sun released the "Seven Sins" of FDT, including breach of fiduciary duty and abuse of customer funds;
3: "56,995 ETH on the verge of liquidation whale" repaid again, and the liquidation price has dropped to 1269.67 US dollars;
4: Ripple acquired cryptocurrency-friendly broker Hidden Road for US$1.25 billion;
5: Bernstein: Bitcoin has shown strong resilience, and institutional adoption will make Bitcoin more robust;
6: US Treasury Secretary Bessant denied urging Trump to change the information on tariffs;
7: Standard Chartered: XRP may reach 12.5 US dollars before the end of Trump's presidency;
8: BlackRock: The market has priced in too many Fed rate cuts;
9: Wall Street tycoon Bill Ackman: Call for a 30-day, 60-day or 90-day pause before tariffs take effect;
10: AI security platform Octane completed $6.75 million seed round, led by Winklevoss Capital and others;
11: Binance CEO: The resurgence of trade protectionism has brought volatility to global markets, and the crypto market is no exception;
12: A whale sold 10,000 ETH, worth $15.71 million;
13: CBOE submitted a 19b-4 form for Canary's SUI ETF application;
14: White House economic adviser Hassett: The Federal Reserve will determine its policy orientation on interest rates;
15: David Sacks, director of encryption and AI at the White House: Black Monday is over;
16: The U.S. Senate held its first trade hearing since Trump announced tariffs;
17: PumpFun deposited 84,358 SOLs worth $9.3 million to Kraken;
18: Market news: a16z seeks to raise $20 billion for its largest fund;
19: OKX is about to launch WCT (WalletConnect);
20: Wall Street brokerage firm Cantor will Coinbase Rating: Overweight;
21: US Trade Representative Jamison Greer: Trump has made it clear that there will be no tariff exemptions in the near future;
22: Wall Street shorts have made a net profit of $127 billion from April 2 to Monday this week;
23: Sources say CoinShares asset management director Frank Spiteri has resigned;
24: Binance Alpha launches Retard Finder Coin (RFC);
25: Fed Goolsby: Tariff implementation far exceeds the Fed's previous model forecast;
26: GMGN Lianchuang: The platform has suffered intermittent traffic attacks that affect user experience, and plans to stop whitelisting some crawler IPs in the future;
27: Trader Eugene: Global trade tariffs may be bearish for risky assets in the long term and will fade out of the crypto market in the short term;
28: Data: TUT leads the March Meme coin list with a 2289% increase;
29: Nikkei 225 index fell 3%; the Korean won against the US dollar hit a 2009 high New low for the year;
30: JPMorgan Chase: A key stock index shows that the probability of a US recession is close to 80%;
31: The US Senate will hold a procedural vote on SEC Chairman nominee Paul Atkins tomorrow;
32: Ripple CTO: Ripple's acquisition of Hidden Road is a decisive moment for XRPL.
